                "sidebar_type": "advice_and_rules",
                "sidebar_heading": "Advice and Rules",
                "image": {
                    "type": "image",
                    "name": "Advice and Rules",
                    "image": "Sidebar_1_AdviceAndRules.png"
                },
                "html": "A spiral centurion might have one of the following glitches. <br/><br/><b>Dulled Blades</b>: Its blade Strike deals only 2d10+5 bludgeoning damage. <br/><b>Misaligned Gears</b>: It loses Rev Up, and if it Strides more than once per round, it takes 1d10 damage. <br/><b>Stuck in a Rut</b>: It uses the same actions each round, regardless of the circumstances."
            }
